All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    BakingStation
    BakingStation allows users to bake items.
    Base
    Core values like screen size, that will need to access, but nothing will need to modify.
    Bin
    Bins allow users to dispose of items.
    CounterTop  
    Customer
    The customer class represents a customer in the game.
    CuttingStation
    CuttingStations allow users to cut Ingredients.
    Dish
    Dishes are used to serve Ingredients.
    ErrorStation
    This class is just used to make level file errors more conspicuous.
    FontHandler
    A convenience class to create fonts that will be used in titles, buttons etc.
    FryingStation
    FryingStations allow users to fry Ingredients.
    GameData
    The GameData class contains globally accessible functions and variables.
    GameLoop
    The GameLoop class is the main game loop.
    ImageMovable
    A class that extends the Image class to allow for images that can be stored in inventory.
    Ingredient
    An ingredient is an item that can be used in a recipe.
    IngredientStation
    IngredientStations provide the player with a supply of ingredients.
    IngredientType
    Represents the various types of Ingredients that the game supports.
    Level
    Reads level environment data from a file and stores it in a 2D array of stations.
    Movable  
    Obstacle
    Obstacles stop the player walking through a specific area
    Physics
    A class that contains static methods for checking collisions and other physics.
    PiazzaPanic
    The main class of the game.
    Player
    The Player class encapsulates player data (position, velocity etc.), but does nothing itself.
    Player.facing
    The direction the player is facing.
    ServingStation
    ServingStation allows users to submit completed Dishes to fulfill orders.
    StageAnimation
    Stores an animation, in the form of frames placed around in a texture.
    StageFactory
    Class responsible for creating stages.
    StageManager
    Manages which stage is "active" (ie is displayed and is responding to user input).
    Station
    Stations allow users to interact with the game environment.
    Vector2
    This class is a simple 2D vector class.
    WidgetFactory
    A collection of convenience functions for creating widgets (all static methods).
